code: public static IsFalseAssertion parse(XContentParser parser) throws IOException {     return new IsFalseAssertion(parser.getTokenLocation(), ParserUtils.parseField(parser)). }

@Override protected void doAssert(Object actualValue, Object expectedValue) {     logger.trace("assert that [{}] doesn't have a true value (field: [{}])", actualValue, getField()).     if (actualValue == null) {         return.     }     String actualString = actualValue.toString().     assertThat(errorMessage(), actualString, anyOf(equalTo(""), equalToIgnoringCase(Boolean.FALSE.toString()), equalTo("0"))). }
private String errorMessage() {     return "field [" + getField() + "] has a true value but it shouldn't". }
